Feature: the poll is an idempotent no-op when no baked dependency has advanced past its current pin

  Pins the idempotence property implied by ADR-022 D2 step 3 — the rebuild +
  republish happens only "if any pin changed". The contrapositive is the
  no-op: when every baked dependency's latest release tag equals the tag
  already pinned in docker/bc-base/Dockerfile, the workflow bumps nothing,
  rebuilds nothing, and republishes nothing — so a scheduled run on an
  up-to-date Dockerfile produces no new bc-base:latest digest and no spurious
  publish. This guards against the failure mode where the scheduled cadence
  itself (scenario 57) churns the registry on every tick. A run that rebuilds
  or republishes :latest despite no pin changing must FAIL this scenario.
  (Targets shopsystem-bc-launcher.)

  @scenario_hash:cf8625dbac93cfdc
  Scenario: a scheduled run where every dependency's latest release already equals its Dockerfile pin makes no change
    Given the bc-base Dockerfile in shopsystem-bc-launcher pins every baked dependency at its current "@vX.Y.Z"
    And for every baked dependency the resolved latest release tag equals the tag already pinned in the Dockerfile
    When the centralized scheduled workflow runs its check-bump-rebuild cycle
    Then the workflow leaves "docker/bc-base/Dockerfile" unchanged with no pin bumped
    And the workflow does not run a bc-base image build
    And the workflow does not republish "ghcr.io/dstengle/shopsystem-bc-base:latest" with a new digest
